<concept id="id_1" class="- topic/topic concept/concept "><title class="- topic/title ">Firefox</title><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><p class="- topic/p ">To use <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Katalon Studio</uicontrol> with Firefox Private Browsing windows, do as follows:</p><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">In <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Katalon Studio</uicontrol>, go to <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Project &gt; Settings &gt; Desired Capabilities &gt; Web UI &gt; Firefox</b>.</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Click <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Add</b> on the command toolbar, then input the following values:</p><table class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry nameend="col3" namest="col1" class="- topic/entry ">Table 1</entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry class="- topic/entry ">Name</entry><entry class="- topic/entry ">Type</entry><entry class="- topic/entry ">Value</entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry class="- topic/entry ">moz:firefoxOptions</entry><entry class="- topic/entry ">Dictionary</entry><entry class="- topic/entry ">Click More (...). In the pop-up <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Dictionary Property Builder</b> dialog, click <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Add</b>, then input values from Table 2.</entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><table class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry nameend="col3" namest="col1" class="- topic/entry ">Table 2</entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry class="- topic/entry ">Name</entry><entry class="- topic/entry ">Type</entry><entry class="- topic/entry ">Value</entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry class="- topic/entry ">args</entry><entry class="- topic/entry ">List</entry><entry class="- topic/entry ">--private</entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><p class="- topic/p "><image href="https://github.com/katalon-studio/docs-images/raw/master/katalon-studio/docs/project-settings-new-ui/KS-DC-FIRFOX-Private-mode.png" scope="external" class="- topic/image "><alt class="- topic/alt ">Open Firefox with devtools in private mode</alt></image></p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Click <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Apply and Close</b>. You can now execute tests in Firefox Private Browsing windows. </p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">To use the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Record and Spy</uicontrol> utility of <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Katalon Studio</uicontrol> in private windows, you need to allow the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Katalon Studio</uicontrol> extension to run in private windows. See Mozilla document: <xref href="https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/extensions-private-browsing" scope="external" class="- topic/xref ">Enabling or disabling extensions in private windows</xref>.</p></li></ol></conbody></concept>